âœ… 1. Ensures Product Availability
A strong supply chain ensures that products are always available at retail outlets. It helps avoid stock-outs or delays, keeping customers satisfied.

ğŸ”¹ Example: FMCG companies like Hindustan Unilever maintain deep rural supply chains to ensure their soaps and shampoos reach even remote villages.

âœ… 2. Reduces Costs
